<DESCRIPT>  FOOD; RECIPE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  HAVING TROUBLE thinking "Christmas" when your mind is still on last week's
Thanksgiving turkey leftovers?;   The remedy is easy. Celebrate the Christmas
spirit with a weekend of fun and feasting at the Livermore Valley Merchants
Christmas Wine Trails. From noon to 5 p.m. Saturday and Sunday, you can tour
the nine Livermore Valley wineries who will host the festive event.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  The Weekly, Part 2  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  LIVERMORE VALLEY WINE FESTIVAL TIME
HORS D'OEUVRES AND GIFTS, TOO  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  The Weekly Cook  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Teamed with local merchants and artisans, participating wineries will
provide you with the opportunity to sample their specially prepared holiday
hors d'oeuvres as well as their wines while you shop on their grounds for
unique holiday gifts.;   Serenaded by musicians playing seasonal music, you
can browse at each site among the best merchandise, hand-made crafts and folk
art that local merchants and artisans have to offer. Local florists, gourmet
shops, candy merchants, toy stores, restaurants, toy stores, book stores and
art stores will round out the roster of participating merchants.;   Talented
craftspeople will be on hand to teach you how to design your own personalized
Christmas gifts. You'll see them demonstrate the intricacies of making grape
wreaths, decorated T-shirts, painted fabric, fresh corsages, toys and cards,
as they display their one-of-a-kind affordably priced gifts.;   To add to the
Christmas spirit, each winery will have its halls decked by local grade-school
students competing for prizes in a Christmas tree decorating contest.;   With
free admission, this may be one of the best holiday bargains of the season.
The events will be held at all the following participating winery tasting
rooms: Cedar Mountain, Chouinard, Concannon, Fenestra, Livermore Valley
Cellars, Retzlaff, and Wente Brothers Estate and Sparkling Wine Cellars. Ivan
Tamas Winery will be at the Bank of Italy building, at First and North
Livermore avenues in Livermore. For more information, call Wente Brothers
Winery at (510) 447-3603 and ask for the tasting room.;   As a preview to
Christmas Wine Trails, the participating wineries have offered their favorite
hors d'oeuvre to try at home for your holiday guests. These and other enticing
recipes will be available for sampling during the event.; PETER'S SPICY
GRILLED PRAWNS; from Concannon Vineyard; 4590 Tesla Road, Livermore; Serve
with Sauvignon Blanc; 1 lb. jumbo prawns, (peeled and deveined); 5 cloves
fresh garlic, minced; 1 crushed red pepper; 2 tablespoons olive oil; Place
olive oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat. When hot, add prawns and
crushed red pepper. Saute 5 minutes or until pink. Slice avocado and top with
chopped cilantro. Serve the avocado slices along with the prawns.; FETA CHEESE
SPREAD; from Livermore Valley Cellars; 1508 Wetmore Rd., Livermore; Serve with
Chardonnay or Fume Blanc; 8 oz. feta cheese, crumbled; 8 oz cream cheese; 3/4
stick butter or margarine; 2 oz. dried tomatoes; 1 glass of white wine; 2-4
cloves fresh garlic, pressed; 1 1/2 teaspoons Italian herbs, (or your favorite
blend; Soften dried tomatoes in the glass of wine. Discard wine. Blend all
ingredients in a food processor using the metal chopping blade until mixture
is almost smooth. Serve on crackers or sliced baguettes.; RED, GREEN AND
WHITE; CHRISTMAS HORS D'OEUVRES; from Cedar Mountain Winery; 7000 Tesla Road,
Livermore; Serve with Chardonnay; 2 packages cream cheese; 2 tablespoons oil;
1/2 cup oil-packed dried tomatoes, drained and chopped; 1/2 cup fresh basil;
Garnishes: basil sprigs, dried tomato slices; Combine chopped basil and oil in
a small bowl and let stand for 1/2 hour. Line a mold or bowl with plastic
wrap. Put 1/3 of the cream cheese into the bottom of the mold. Layer with the
chopped oil-packed dried tomatoes. Layer with 1/3 of the cream cheese, then
the chopped basil and oil mixture and top with the remaining cream cheese.
Chill in refrigerator for two hours. Unmold onto serving dish. Garnish if
desired. Serve with sliced baguettes. Yields 2 cups.; FENESTRA'S SMOKED;
SALMON MOUSSE; from Fenestra Winery; 83 E. Vallecitos Rd.,; Livermore; Serve
with Chardonnay; 1/4 lb. smoked salmon, cut into pieces; 1/2 cup whipping
cream; 1/4 cup melted unsalted butter; 1 teaspoon lemon juice, or more to
taste; Process smoked salmon and whipping cream in food processor until
smooth. Add melted butter and blend. Add lemon juice, blend and put in crock
or small bowl. Garnish with capers. Chill completely and serve with crackers.;
SPICY VEGETABLE DIP; from Retzlaff Vineyards; 1356 South Livermore Ave.,
Livermore; Serve with Chardonnay; 1 (15 oz.) can garbanzo beans, drained; 2
tablespoons olive oil; 1 tablespoon Retzlaff Chardonnay; 2 tablespoons chopped
onion; 1/2 teaspoon salt; 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce; 2 tablespoons
sesame seeds; dash Tabasco sauce; 2 tablespoons chopped parsley; In food
processor fitted with the metal chopping blade, process beans oil, wine and
onion. Process until smooth. Add salt, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and
sesame seeds. Process briefly. Spoon into a small serving dish. Sprinkle with
parsley. Serve with vegetables or chips.  </TEXT>
